template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-arkansas
name: Employee Restrictive Covenant (Arkansas)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  Arkansas-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement built for Ark. Code
  Ann. section 4-75-101: confidentiality and trade-secret protection, employee
  and customer non-solicitation, a non-dealing covenant, and an optional
  non-compete drawn to the statutory protectable-interest and time-and-scope
  test. Recites the statutory categories of protectable business interest, keeps
  durations within the two-year presumptively-reasonable window, relies on the
  continued-employment consideration rule, voids any practice restriction on a
  physician under the 2025 amendment, flags the Title 17, Subtitle 3
  licensed-professional exclusion, and acknowledges the mandatory judicial
  reformation remedy. Drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel review.
